    <item>
      <title>Re: Some incentive to be good in China</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=OT&amp;message.id=153894#M153894</link>
      <description>&lt;P&gt;There is an inalienable right to a person's body, and, as with the rest of human society, you have to give your consent before you can start being used as a Mr. Potato Head.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The death penalty isn't meant to be a deterrent or a kind of irony, it's meant to be "You've become a risk to society, and the result is that you're going to be removed from it".&amp;nbsp; This penalty does not remove the right to keeping your organs where they are.&amp;nbsp; You don't kill someone for the advantage of harvesting their organs, you kill them as a consequence to their actions, the sentence is not "You shall be hung from the neck until you are dead, and then your organs shall be removed and sold to high profile individuals". &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Since they are &lt;EM&gt;your&lt;/EM&gt; organs, it's up to &lt;EM&gt;you&lt;/EM&gt; whether or not they can be removed and donated after death, it's not up to the prison or the government.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
